The license key is required for Feature Pack, Collaboration Pack, as well as the Productivity Pack.

Select the authorization suitable type for your features. The access key-based authorization is highly recommended and the best option in a production environment. The development token should rather be used for testing purposes. The authorization credentials are required for Real-time collaboration or Import from Word, and optional for Export to Word/PDF to generate documents without the watermark.
The environment management panel can be found in CKEditor dashboard .
The access key for the environment can be found in the CKEditor dashboard .

Use the development token URL only for testing purposes. It does not provide full permission validation.</br>For production environments, it is strongly recommended to use the Environment ID and Access Key instead.

The Organization ID is available in the CKEditor dashboard .

To use real-time collaboration features—such as comments, track changes, and revision history — you must disable the Source Editing plugin, as raw HTML editing is not compatible with the collaboration engine
Additionally, you must save the RTE content at least once before making any edits. Without this initial save, comments, track changes, or revision history data may be lost.

The toolbar configuration from your YAML preset is now managed by the CKEditor Pack extension's drag-and-drop toolbar interface. This means that, at runtime, the CKEditor Pack configuration takes precedence and defines the active toolbar — your YAML file remains intact but is no longer the source for toolbar rendering.
